    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Bulbophyllum kenejiense are attributed to its antimicrobial activity, which is responsible for inhibiting the growth of various pathogens. This plant exhibits anti-inflammatory properties, reducing inflammation and alleviating pain in affected areas. The antimicrobial properties also translate to its antifungal and antibacterial properties, offering protection against infections caused by fungi and bacteria. Additionally, Bulbophyllum kenejiense has been found to possess antioxidant properties, neutralizing free radicals and preventing oxidative stress. Flavonoids, alkaloids, and terpenoids in this plant are responsible for its medicinal properties, including its anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and antioxidant activities.",
