    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Bulbophyllum kenejiense are flavonoids, alkaloids, terpenoids, and phenolic compounds. Flavonoids, specifically kaempferol and quercetin, exhibit antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities, contributing to the plant's medicinal properties. Alkaloids, such as berberine and palmatine, have antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory effects, while terpenoids, including limonene and pinene, display antimicrobial and antifungal properties. The phenolic compounds, including gallic acid and ferulic acid, also exhibit antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities, further supporting the plant's medicinal uses. These bioactive compounds work in synergy to provide the plant's therapeutic benefits, making Bulbophyllum kenejiense a valuable resource in traditional medicine.",
